cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of computing geodesic centers of a polygonal domain, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper proposes an algorithm for computing all geodesic centers in polynomial time.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possibility as the paper mentions the concept of shortest path maps, which are used in game theory for analyzing the behavior of players in games.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper discusses the $\pi$-range property on shortest path lengths, which is related to the study of control systems.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possibility as the paper proposes an algorithm for computing geodesic centers, which involves numerical computations.
